El 41% de los norteamericanos tienen un teléfono con cámara
En la noticia dice americanos, pero claramente no se refiere a todos los americanos.

<blockquote>
<a href="http://blogs.zdnet.com/ITFacts/?p=12805" rel="bookmark" title="Permalink"> 41% of Americans have a cameraphone</a> by <a href="http://zdnet.com">ZDNet</a>'s ZDNet Research -- 41% of American households own a camera phone, Parks Associates says. Gartner predicts that about 589 mln cell phones will be sold with cameras in 2007, increasing to more than 1 bln worldwide by 2010.
</blockquote>


